<recipe>
<title>
Strawberry Pretzel Fluff
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 10 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
SERVINGS: 14 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
8 ounce container non-dairy whipped topping I used TruWhip.
10 ounce package mini marshmallows
2 cups plain nonfat Greek yogurt
3 cup strawberries, quartered
2 cups thin pretzel sticks, broken
</ingredients>
<instructions>
In a large bowl, mix together whipped topping, marshmallows, and Greek yogurt until well-combined.
Toss in strawberries and pretzels. If you want the pretzels to stay crunchy, wait to add until just before serving.
Cover, and refrigerate until ready to serve.
</instructions>
</recipe>
